namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the own print shop.
In this video, we will walk you through the enhancements we have made for the B to B or private stores and public stores such as franchise and Reseller.
In this release, let us walk you through the enhancements 1 by 1.
Talking about the B to B or private stores, we have extended the Product content override feature for the store admins.

So in the admin panel, when the store admin logs into their accounts, they can see the gallery menu added to the action drop down along with the Product Categories menu under the Product section on the edit page.
They can now override the product name and its URL and search keywords from the edit screen.
They can now also upload and manage the gallery images product wise.
The gallery setting set by the Super Admin will be considered here.
The store admin will be able to verify the same.
Along with these, two products can now be displayed within their categories.
For this, the store admin panel will have a Product categories menu under the Product section.
From the product category page, when you click on the edit icon, you will be able to override the category title and category URL.

Also under the configuration section, Store admin can choose to keep the default or store specific settings for category badge pattern, promotional text on the title, category promotional text, sorting status, homepage display as well as add to cart option.
If you want, you can also manage the description section for the respective product categories next to Store Wise Currency Management and display in the Admin panel.
When the admin is set up custom currency for different stores and customers from those stores place orders.
Then in the Order listing page, the Super admin will be able to see the individual currencies in the Total Amount column.
To display Store wise currency.
We have a new setting in the site settings where the admin can choose to display default, Set currency or Store Wise currency.
Now talking about the specific change in the Franchise and Reseller modules, a provision is provided to set up Tax Wet.

From the settings screen, the admin can choose to set up default or store specific configuration and once this is configured, a new menu of Tax wet settings will appear under Store Configuration and Product sections.
Once the store admin is logged in their store accounts.
Similar to store wise currency, store wise time zones can also be managed.
For this one setting.
Store wise local time zone has been added to the site settings and in the configuration section of stores, from the settings screen, you can choose to set up default or store specific time zones.
Once done in the admin panel, the store wise time zone will be displayed on the Order listing page, quote listing page, and the bottom of the screen.
So that was all we have brought for B to B private and Franchise reseller accounts.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
